{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Root cause**: The DSL parser stores prompt values with a `file(\"...\")` wrapper (e.g. `file(\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\")`), but the step content API handler was using the raw value as a file path. Additionally, the handler checked for `command`/`script` config keys, but the DSL uses `run`.","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401354435Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401370445Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"**Changes:**","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401374022Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401377328Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"1. **`handler.go:1177-1184`** — Extract file path from `file(\"...\")` wrapper before reading prompt files","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401380504Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"2. **`handler.go:1186-1189`** — Check `run` config key (matching the DSL) instead of `command`","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.4013888Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"3. **`handler.go:1190-1198`** — Also apply `extractFileRef` to `script` config values","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401398077Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"4. **`handler.go:1204-1213`** — Added `extractFileRef()` helper to parse the `file(\"...\")` DSL syntax","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401402776Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","message":"5. **`project_detail.html:263`** — Added `run` to the config key filter so script step commands display in the drawer","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401417905Z"}
{"type":"log","step_name":"implement","timestamp":"2026-03-08T04:18:10.401429216Z"}
